This annotation is ongoing via our web site, http://gun-violence.org/ , and the GVDB will be regu- larly updated with new data and new layers of annotation, making it a valuable resource for public health, public pol- icy, and social science researchers interested in understand- ing and preventing gun violence.
The latest version of the database will be maintained and available for download at http://gun-violence.org/ .
